w this is where I tip my hat to Russian Railroads. I''ve played it maybe 6x at the time of this writing and I''ve yet to crack the "most efficient" strategy. The beauty of the game is that there are a lot of options to choose from. You can go focus on just 2 railroads and maximize their benefits, or be a jack of all trades and focus on both railroads and factories. At the very least, the replay value ramps up once you finish a game or two with players who also love the game. It''s not a play another game right after the first one kind-of-thing but it''s more of a let''s plan another game session of this because I want to score better.', 'Russian Railroads', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '117-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-03-16 14:16:48', '2017-03-16 14:16:48', '', 117, 'http://localhost/meepler/?p=120', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
